              <span id="reviewTextContainer10267124" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2532499031828165739">A manager at Barnes &amp; Nobles told me that this was a great book because it shifted blame for the problems of the poor onto the poor, thus holding them accountable and providing room for personal responsibility. Hardly a compelling case for me! So for a long time, I didn’t read it. But now I have, and what the B&amp;N guy said was a gross oversimplification and misreading. More thoughts here:<br/><br/><a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://alisonkinney.com/2015/07/24/david-shipler-the-working-poor-invisible-in-america-read-dec-2007/'>http://alisonkinney.com/2015/07/24/da...</a><br/><br/>It&apos;s a great book.</span>
  <span id="freeText2532499031828165739" style="display:none">A manager at Barnes &amp; Nobles told me that this was a great book because it shifted blame for the problems of the poor onto the poor, thus holding them accountable and providing room for personal responsibility. Hardly a compelling case for me! So for a long time, I didn’t read it. But now I have, and what the B&amp;N guy said was a gross oversimplification and misreading. More thoughts here:<br /><br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://alisonkinney.com/2015/07/24/david-shipler-the-working-poor-invisible-in-america-read-dec-2007/">http://alisonkinney.com/2015/07/24/da...</a><br /><br />It's a great book.</span>
