<div id="review_1212479326" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1212479326" />
    <a title="Rebecca" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/38713938-rebecca"><img alt="Rebecca" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1422413715p2/38713938.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1212479326?book_show_action=true">Feb 26, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rebecca" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rebecca" href="/user/show/38713938-rebecca">Rebecca</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1212479326" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11415829384496554096">I work in a non-profit, and we read this for our most recent office book club.<br/><br/>If you don&apos;t know anything about the lives of poor people living in the United States, you might find that this book shines light on issues you&apos;ve rarely considered. The book is written as a collection of stories, grouped by theme, about the lives of people whom the author interviews repeatedly over the span of a few years. These stories may help you see the working poor and their various situations from another perspe</span>
  <span id="freeText11415829384496554096" style="display:none">I work in a non-profit, and we read this for our most recent office book club.<br /><br />If you don't know anything about the lives of poor people living in the United States, you might find that this book shines light on issues you've rarely considered. The book is written as a collection of stories, grouped by theme, about the lives of people whom the author interviews repeatedly over the span of a few years. These stories may help you see the working poor and their various situations from another perspective.<br /><br />If you have working knowledge of what it's like to live as a poor person in the USA, I suggest skipping this one. The collection of stories shows many of the symptoms of poverty, but it never ties together completely enough to identify and address the root cause of poverty in the United States. No solutions are offered. It sometimes falls into the trap of telling a single story. Yes, poverty can be utterly horrible. No, the lives of all poor people are not horrible. <br /><br />On a personal note, I was sometimes bothered by language the author used and occasionally felt the book was bordering on becoming Ruby Payne-esque. The word "illegal" is sometimes used in place of "undocumented" which always makes my blood boil.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="11415829384496554096" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

